markdown: 3 II. ASSISTANCE OUTSIDE DEVELOPMENT A. Received the the complete data for the second interlaboratory study of monitor I-13. The initial analysis has been completed and a preliminary memo issued giving targets and control chart values of the composite results and for individual labs. The other statistical analyses have also been completed and a report is being drafted. (Jones) B. Started analysis of data for the I-13 monitor calibration on CO, NO, HCN and RCHO gas phase analysis. (Jones) III. OTHER A. Serving on the R&D BOB Committee and Trivia Questionnaire subcommittee. (Johnston) B. Provided miscellaneous statistical, economic, demographic, socio-economic, and product use information and consultations. (Jones, Martin, Ryan, Johnston) D. Visited VCU to interview candidates for a Summer Intern position working on the consumer expenditure data.
